&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;What I mean is... if SOE can afford to sell less copies of the expansions, then&amp;nbsp; why do they have to charge a higher price. I thought the law of economics was... the more you sell, the lower the cost per item so you can provide a lower price.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;EQ isn't exactly growing in population. I would venture to guess that the majority of The Combine's population is going to be comming from the current population.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;People will be leaving there servers to join a new one that requires an expansion to be broken before the next one can be played. Unless we have an uber guild that is going to plow through the entire game (One guild in EQ broke GoD pre-OoW. Did anyone beat OoW pre-DoN?) and unlock it in a few months, I don't see how the new expansions are going to sell very well. SOE said they wanted to release two expansions per year. If the expansion is not unlocked, why buy it?&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I am curious of what the devs think of the progression server and such an issue. What would it do to our expansion prices and if SOE will continue to offer EQ if they can't sell the expansions they cram down our throats before we are ready for them.&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
